1. Scenario: You committed code with sensitive data (like a password or API key) and pushed to GitHub. What will you do?
2.In GitHub, â€œrotate credentialsâ€ means replacing your old authentication tokens, SSH keys, or passwords with new ones to reduce security risks.
  Why rotate credentials?
  Compromised keys/tokens â†’ If your personal access token (PAT), SSH key, or GitHub App secret is leaked.
Best practice â†’ Even if not leaked, rotating (regenerating) credentials periodically keeps your account secure.
Compliance â†’ Some companies require rotation every 30/60/90 days.

